Sometimes, STEM fields and the liberal arts just can't seem to understand each other.
I'm not trying to take sides here; just take this as the random rambling of a regular liberal arts person.

When you explain things to us in jargon, we don't even know what it is we don't know.
We ask a question because we're confused, but when you talk about knowledge or fields we've never studied as if it's common sense—using the language of that specific domain—we don't even have the program installed to understand those words in the first place.
It's like... we're throwing a 404 error.
(404 Not Found = That program does not exist in the liberal arts OS directory.)

I noticed something while chatting with Gemini.
That guy talks in a friendly tone, but underneath it all, his communication style is hardcore STEM.
And the conclusion I reached is that the tech crowd and liberal arts majors are running on completely different OS architectures from the start. We speak entirely different languages.

